%I A396419 #12 Jul 02 2026 21:56:02
%S A396419 3,8,11,14,16,18,20,22,25,27,27
%N A396419 a(n) is the most primes produced by any n-digit prime according to rules stipulated in Honaker's A048853.
%C A396419 Also, the maximum of A048853 taken over all n-digit primes.
%H A396419 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="https://wp.technologyreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MIT-Alumni-News-Puzzle-Corner-March-April-2026.pdf">Puzzle Corner: Problem M/A2. Most neighborly prime</a>, MIT Technology Review, March/April 2026; <a href="https://wp.technologyreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/MIT-Alumni-News-Puzzle-Corner-July-August2026.pdf">Solution</a>, ibid., July/August 2026.
%F A396419 a(n) = A048853(A396418(n)).
%F A396419 a(n) = max_{10^(d-1) <= p prime < 10^d} A048853(p).
%Y A396419 Cf. A048853, A050673, A396418.
%K A396419 nonn,base,more,changed
%O A396419 1,1
%A A396419 _Michael S. Branicky_, May 26 2026
